line_1: Here, Richard, let my Scheme commence.
line_2: Oh! may my Words be lost in Sense;
By turns we reason, or submit to sense,

line_1: O shield me, sapience! virtue's reign commence!
line_2: How bless'd a change! a long adieu to sense:

line_1: Know Sir, when friendship does commence,
line_2: All flatt'ry must be spurn'd from thence:

line_1: Doth his long weary Pilgrimage commence:

line_1: "Delight of either sex! thy reign commence;
line_2: " With balmy sweetness soothe the weary sense,

line_1: Ere Britain saw the foul revolt commence,
line_2: And treach'rous Wit began her war with Sense.

line_2: An Acquaintance with all Men of Spirit and Sense;

line_2: Here see, acquitted of all vain pretence,

line_1: Tops whip'd by school-boys sages must commence,

line_1: 'Tis yours this night to bid the reign commence
line_2: Of rescu'd nature, and reviving sense;
